ān</i> ‘stone, rock’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’. This surname has been established in Ireland since the 16th century, where it is also found under the variant <i>Stankard</i>.","History: An early bearer of this surname in North America, Thomas Stanford of England, settled in Charlestown, MA, in the mid 17th century and started a family line that includes Leland Stanford (1824–93), the railroad developer who was governor of CA, a US senator, and the founding benefactor of Stanford University."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Stainford was born in 1160, in Aldingham, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. John Stainford. He died in 1220, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1160–1220":"1160–1220","1164–Female":"1164–Surnud","1178–1237":"1178–1237","1237":"1237","1178":"1178","1220":"1220","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1160–1220":"1160–1220","1164–Female":"1164–Kuollut","1178–1237":"1178–1237","1237":"1237","1178":"1178","1220":"1220","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1160–1220":"1160–1220","1164–Female":"1164–Décédée","1178–1237":"1178–1237","1237":"1237","1178":"1178","1220":"1220","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"John Stainford est né en 1160, à Aldingham, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. John Stainford. Il est décédé en 1220, à l’âge de 60 ans."},"de":{"1160–1220":"1160–1220","1164–Female":"1164–Verstorben","1178–1237":"1178–1237","1237":"1237","1178":"1178","1220":"1220","1164":"1164","1160":"1160","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, L